{
  "texts": [
    "Each of these latents is incrementally updated layer by layer by adding a residual.",
    "The residual added to the latent at position i in layer j is a function f j of all preceding tokens' latents h",
    "where the resulting vector h (j) i is still of dimension d. The function f j itself, called a transformer block, is composed of a masked self-attention layer followed by a feed-forward layer with a residual connection and root mean square (RMS) normalization in between (Vaswani et al., 2017; Touvron et al., 2023).",
    "Due to RMS normalization, all latents lie on a d-dimensional hypersphere of radius √ d. In pretraining, all transformer blocks f 1,.",
    ", f m (with m the number of layers) are tuned such that the final latent h (m) i for position i is well-suited for predicting the token at position i + 1."
  ]
}